What you need to know:  Djokovic said he was "sad" with how events played out in Australia, where he spent days in detention at a notorious immigration hotel."I was really sad and disappointed with the way it all ended for me in Australia," he said. "It wasn't easy."The reason why I was deported from Australia was because the minister for immigration used his discretion to cancel my visa based on his perception that I might create some anti-vax sentiment in the country or in the city, which I completely disagree with."